verses.roman:
ācārya gosāñi caitanyera mukhya aṅga
āra eka aṅga tāṅra prabhu nityānanda

synonyms: ācārya gosāñi—Advaita Ācārya; caitanyera—of Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; mukhya—primary; aṅga—part; āra—another; eka—one; aṅga—part; tāṅra—of Lord Caitanya Mahāprabhu; prabhu nityānanda—Lord Nityānanda.
translation: Śrī Advaita Ācārya is a principal limb of Lord Caitanya. Another limb of the Lord is Nityānanda Prabhu.
